Class AVLTree<E>

  • java.lang.Object
    • AVLTree<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of elements maintained by this set

    public class AVLTree<E>
extends java.lang.Object
    An AVL binary tree. Made by Brock Davis March 2017 Unlike the Java TreeSet, this implementation allows duplicates Values equal to a node will move to the right, and removing a value will remove the rightmost node

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      AVLTree()
      Constructs a new, empty tree, sorted according to the natural ordering of its elements.

      int size()
      Returns how many elements are in the tree
      java.lang.String toString()
      Returns the String representation of the string The form is (leftTree) root [rightTree] This form is recursively called for each subtree An example of this would be ((1) 4 [(7) 10]) 15 [(18) 20]
